<TITLE> Zimbabwe confiscates Tsvangirai's passport </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 HARARE, Thu Aug 14, (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Zimbabwe authorities confiscated the passports of opposition leader Morgan Tsvangirai and other MDC officials at Harare airport, the party said on Thursday. "They have taken our passports. This is a reflection of their insincerity. They want to talk to us yet they behave like hooligans," Movement for Democratic Change Secretary-General Tendai Biti told reporters. The MDC said Tsvangirai was due to travel to South Africa to attend a summit of regional grouping SADC after power-sharing talks with President Robert Mugabe stalled this week
